<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 1: Create EventSwitcher component</name>
  <files>src/components/dashboard/EventSwitcher.tsx</files>
  <action>
Create `src/components/dashboard/EventSwitcher.tsx` — a dropdown component for switching between events.

**Visibility logic (NAV-02):**
- Consumes `useEventContext()` for `events`, `currentEvent`, `switchEvent`
- Consumes `useAuth()` for `isSuperAdmin`
- Computes `showSwitcher = events.length > 1 || isSuperAdmin`
- If `!showSwitcher`, return `null` (renders nothing)

**Trigger button:**
- Displays current event label: `partner1_name & partner2_name` if both exist, else `slug` as fallback
- Append a `ChevronDown` icon from `lucide-react` (rotate 180deg when open)
- Styling: `font-brand text-sm text-slate-700` with hover state, rounded-lg padding matching nav tab sizing

**Dropdown panel:**
- Uses `useState<boolean>` for open/closed state
- Uses `useRef<HTMLDivElement>` + `useEffect` mousedown listener for click-outside dismiss (copy the exact pattern from Dashboard.tsx column visibility dropdown as noted in RESEARCH.md)
- Positioned with CSS `absolute` below the trigger, `right-0` (RTL-aware start edge), `z-50`, `mt-1`
- White background, rounded-xl, shadow-lg, border border-slate-200, `min-w-[220px]`
- Max height `max-h-64 overflow-y-auto` for users with many events

**Event list items (NAV-01):**
- Each item shows: event label (`partner1_name & partner2_name` or `slug`) and a small status badge (`draft` in amber, `active` in emerald) using a `<span>` with `text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-full`
- Current event gets `bg-violet-50 text-violet-700 font-medium` background
- Other events get `hover:bg-slate-50 text-slate-700`
- On click: call `switchEvent(event.id)` and `setOpen(false)`

**"Create New Event" footer (NAV-03):**
- Separated from event list by a `border-t border-slate-100` divider
- Shows a `Plus` icon from `lucide-react` + text "אירוע חדש" (Hebrew for "New Event")
- On click: `navigate('/onboarding')` using `useNavigate` from react-router-dom
- Styling: `text-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-50` with `px-3 py-2` padding

**Helper function:**
- `eventLabel(event: EventData): string` — returns `partner1_name & partner2_name` if both exist, else `event.slug`
- Define inside the file (not exported — internal only)

Use Tailwind classes only. No new dependencies. RTL-aware (the component sits inside an RTL nav).
  </action>
